Number of storage units per fid.

params.fid: The fid that will receive the credit.
params.units: Number of storage units to credit.

params.fid: The fid that will receive the storage units.
params.units: Number of storage units to rent.

params.timestamp: The new deprecationTimestamp. Must be at least equal to block.timestamp.

params.fixedPrice: The new fixed ETH/USD price. Fixed point value with 8 decimals.                   Setting this value back to zero from a nonzero value will                   re-enable the price feed.

params.maxPrice: The new priceFeedMaxAnswer. Must be greater than current priceFeedMinAnswer.

params.max: The new maximum supply of storage units.

params.minPrice: The new priceFeedMinAnswer. Must be less than current priceFeedMaxAnswer.

params.usdPrice: The new unit price in USD. Fixed point value with 8 decimals.

params.amount: The amount of ether to withdraw.

VERSION().notice: Contract version specified in the Farcaster protocol version scheme.

batchCredit(uint256[],uint256).notice: Credit multiple fids with free storage units. Only callable by operator.

batchRent(uint256[],uint256[]).notice: Rent storage for multiple fids for a year. The caller must provide at least         price(units) wei of payment where units is the sum of storage units requested across         the fids. See comments on rent() for additional details.

continuousCredit(uint256,uint256,uint256.notice: Credit a continuous sequence of fids with free storage units. Only callable by operator.

credit(uint256,uint256).notice: Credit a single fid with free storage units. Only callable by operator.

deprecationTimestamp().notice: Block timestamp at which this contract will no longer accept storage rent payments.         Changeable by owner.

fixedEthUsdPrice().notice: A fixed ETH/USD price which overrides the Chainlink feed. If this value is nonzero,         we disable external calls to the price feed and use this price. Changeable by owner.         To be used in the event of a price feed failure.

lastPriceFeedUpdateBlock().notice: Block number of the last update to ethUsdPrice.

lastPriceFeedUpdateTime().notice: Timestamp of the last update to ethUsdPrice.

maxUnits().notice: Total capacity of storage units. Changeable by owner.

pause().notice: Pause, disabling rentals and credits.         Only callable by owner.

price(uint256).notice: Calculate the cost in wei to rent the given number of storage units.

priceFeedCacheDuration().notice: Duration to cache ethUsdPrice before updating from the price feed. Changeable by owner.

priceFeedMaxAge().notice: Max age of a price feed answer before it is considered stale. Changeable by owner.

priceFeedMaxAnswer().notice: Upper bound on acceptable price feed answer. Changeable by owner.

priceFeedMinAnswer().notice: Lower bound on acceptable price feed answer. Changeable by owner.

refreshPrice().notice: Force refresh the cached Chainlink ETH/USD price. Callable by owner and treasurer.

rent(uint256,uint256).notice: Rent storage for a given fid for a year. The caller must provide at least         price(units) wei of payment. Any excess payment will be refunded to the caller. Hubs         will issue storage for 365 days + 30 day grace period after which it expires.         RentedUnits is never decremented on the contract even as the assigned storage expires         on the hubs. This is done to keep the contract simple since we expect to launch a new         storage contract within the year and deprecate this one. Even if that does not occur,         the existing maxUnits parameter can be tweaked to account for expired units.

rentedUnits().notice: Total number of storage units that have been rented.

setCacheDuration(uint256).notice: Change the priceFeedCacheDuration. Only callable by owner.

setDeprecationTimestamp(uint256).notice: Change the deprecationTimestamp. Only callable by owner.

setFixedEthUsdPrice(uint256).notice: Set the fixed ETH/USD price, disabling the price feed if the value is         nonzero. This is an emergency fallback in case of a price feed failure.         Only callable by owner.

setGracePeriod(uint256).notice: Change the uptimeFeedGracePeriod. Only callable by owner.

setMaxAge(uint256).notice: Change the priceFeedMaxAge. Only callable by owner.

setMaxAnswer(uint256).notice: Change the priceFeedMaxAnswer. Only callable by owner.

setMaxUnits(uint256).notice: Change the maximum supply of storage units. Only callable by owner.

setMinAnswer(uint256).notice: Change the priceFeedMinAnswer. Only callable by owner.

setPrice(uint256).notice: Change the USD price per storage unit. Callable by owner.

setPriceFeed(address).notice: Change the price feed addresss. Callable by owner.

setUptimeFeed(address).notice: Change the uptime feed addresss. Callable by owner.

setVault(address).notice: Change the vault address that can receive funds from this contract.         Only callable by owner.

unitPrice().notice: Calculate the cost in wei to rent one storage unit.

unpause().notice: Unpause, enabling rentals and credits.         Only callable by owner.

uptimeFeedGracePeriod().notice: Period in seconds to wait after the L2 sequencer restarts before resuming rentals.         See: https://docs.chain.link/data-feeds/l2-sequencer-feeds. Changeable by owner.

usdUnitPrice().notice: Price per storage unit in USD. Fixed point value with 8 decimals, e.g. 5e8 = $5 USD.         Changeable by owner.

vault().notice: Address to which the treasurer role can withdraw funds. Changeable by owner.

withdraw(uint256).notice: Withdraw a specified amount of ether from the contract balance to the vault.         Only callable by treasurer.
